  "Design, Monitor, Assess, Investigate, Correct": "",
  "Define, Measure, Analyze, Improve, Control": "",
  "Detect, Maintain, Apply, Install, Check": "",
  "Data, Mean, Average, Index, Capability": "",
  "DMAIC is the Six Sigma methodology: Define the problem, Measure key data, Analyze root causes, Improve the process, and Control to sustain gains.": "",
  "What distribution is used to model defect counts in quality control when defects are rare?": "",
  "The Poisson distribution, since defects are rare and independent": "",
  "The exponential distribution": "",
  "The uniform distribution": "",
  "The normal distribution only": "",
  "When defects are rare and occur independently at a constant rate per unit, the Poisson distribution is the appropriate model.": "",
